<reference id="alt" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>alt</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>alt</xmlelement> element provides alternate text for an image. It is
        equivalent to the <xmlatt>alt</xmlatt> attribute on the <xmlelement>image</xmlelement>
        element; since the <xmlatt>alt</xmlatt> attribute is deprecated, use the
            <xmlelement>alt</xmlelement> element instead. The <xmlelement>alt</xmlelement> element
        can be more easily edited or translated than the <xmlatt>alt</xmlatt> attribute.</shortdesc>
